# Motion Animation Patterns

## Import

ALWAYS import from `"motion/react"`, NEVER from `"framer-motion"`:

```tsx
import { motion, useScroll, useTransform, useInView, AnimatePresence } from "motion/react"
```

Mark animated components with `"use client"`.

## Scroll Reveals (whileInView)

```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6, ease: "easeOut" }}
>
```

For staggered lists, increment `delay`:

```tsx
{items.map((item, i) => (
  <motion.div
    key={item.id}
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
    whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    viewport={{ once: true }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.5, delay: i * 0.08 }}
  />
))}
```

## Scroll-Linked Parallax

```tsx
const ref = useRef(null)
const { scrollYProgress } = useScroll({ target: ref, offset: ["start end", "end start"] })
const y = useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0, 1], [50, -50])

<motion.div ref={ref} style={{ y }} />
```

## Performance Rules

- Only animate `opacity`, `transform`, `filter`, `clipPath` (GPU-composited)
- Use `will-change: transform` sparingly and only during active animation
- Prefer `viewport={{ once: true }}` to avoid re-triggering
- Keep durations 0.4-0.8s for reveals, 0.15-0.25s for hovers
- Use spring physics for natural feel: `{ type: "spring", stiffness: 100, damping: 20 }`
